The paper focuses on the application of deep reinforcement learning in real-time strategy games, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of convolutional neural networks for feature extraction also suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the performance of the game environment on high-end consumer hardware, which could be relevant to graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper mentions the flexibility of the game environment for different scenarios, which could relate to genetic algorithms (cs.GA) and machine learning (cs.LG).
